			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1603455">
									

<p>As for the whole fictional character bit, well, we <strong>do</strong> have an SCP that is the angel guarding what appears to be the Garden of Eden&#8230;.</p>
<p>And though yes, this is totally a work of fiction and whatnot, it's still interesting to me to link 076 and 073 to the Bible. Given the original story of Cain and Abel, there are all kinds of wonderful interpretations you can make. It could be that the story within the Bible got totally flipped about and twisted around, true. But the interpretation I rather prefer is that Cain got his punishment, and became a rather remorseful, polite fellow indeed over his time on the earth. Abel, originally a far kinder fellow, made a deal with something&#8230; <strong>else&#8230;</strong> to survive, and in doing so has become the monstrous fighting machine we all know now.</p>

